<br>
There are two parts of this:  punishment for the wrongdoer and reimbursement for the victim.  If the victim cannot be identified, then reimbursement is a moot point.  That only leaves the punishment to be decided.  Since the two can't be tied together because of lack of identity of the true victime, then I like the idea of the money going towards expenses of the next raid.  Either way, the miscreant should have to forfeit the money gained from the transaction.  Actions must have consequences if they are not to be repeated.<br>
<br>
