</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaritzia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maritzia</A> at: 7/18/02 2:04:05 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujarkellraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 960<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/18/02 2:05:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2350.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Easy to say Sorry.</span><hr size=1> A few thoughts. <br>
<br>
First of all, I'm 52, I'm rather well equiped, and I use these gauntlets (I won them on my first Naggy Raid, and I still wear them).   I wear them over Crystal Chitten due to the fact that in raids I need 7 sta, 7 disease, 7 dex, and 7 poison  more than 10 ac (I don't get hit much, I'm a rogue... but I need all the HPs I can get, and those saves are quite nice).  These are quite good gauntlets here, so let's not pretend this was some Crystaline Spear here.<br>
<br>
Two, in an open raid situation, you can't make special cases for people.  This wasn't a guild raid, you can't just watch this person in the future.  You NEED to post their name to warn other open raid leaders, and you NEED to make an example of them so that it doesn't become common place, otherwise it becomes a slippery slope, where you forgave the last one so you have to forgive the next clown who pulls this stunt.  I don't buy ignorance.  You walk into a raid where loot distribution is clear, then pull this... no way.  I know people don't listen some times... but if there's one thing I know well, it's that everybody listens to the loot arangement, especially people who are active on the sellers' market, which this person obviously is.  <br>
<br>
I would not take this person on future open raids, ever.  If they returned the money they got, I would forgive them, yes... but forgiving and forgetting are two different things.  I may not dislike them if they do what's honorable after making the mistake, but I still wouldn't let them back on the open raids... perhaps that way others wouldn't make the same mistake.<br>
<br>
This may seem hard line or unforgiving... but in cases where money is concerned, even virtual money, there are people who will take advantage of any loop hole or advantage, and letting someone off the hook cause they said sorry is a huge loop hole that I wouldn't want opened up.<br>
<br>
Jarkell Ravensteel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usimanmistrunner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SimanMistrunner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 139<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/18/02 2:30:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2350.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Easy to say Sorry.</span><hr size=1> In my opinion, it is clear this guy should be banned from open raids until he either returns the gloves or the pp he earned from the sale of the gloves.  If he is not willing to do that, how can you say he is really sorry?  <br>
<br>
As has been mentioned previously, the one thing about raids that everyone (and I mean everyone) has an understanding of is LOOT.  People will skip through or barely parse over strategy discussions, background information and group alignments but the one thing that folks always hone in on is loot distribution.  That is what motivates people to spend several hours of their time to raid.  You are honestly telling me that a guy who is active on the market didn't have any idea how loot distribution worked for this raid?<br>
<br>
Perhaps I am too cynical, but I don't buy it for a second that this guy did not know about need before greed or what it meant.  Particularly someone who knows about the marketplace here and has an offer to sell those gauntlets the very day after the raid.<br>
