<br>
Secondly, Saying sorry is easy, right then, its a damn shame so many people both in RL and EQ never manage to say sorry. You got it folks, most folks do not say sorry, many people in this position would of been more likely to f*(&amp; you than sorry.<br>
<br>
I agree with many that sorry is not eneough, but thats because of how I would react. God I would be so guilt ridden if I had screwed up this way, well I would be a pain to be near :-)<br>
<br>
As to folks not knowing what NBG is, alas many do not, have run raids where person X rolls on item Y and its obvious that X will not use Y, I tend to have a little chat and normaly people get it.<br>
<br>
A suggestion, when awarding items have a quick look at the person before you hand it over, that always works well.<br>
<br>
Another better solution is the update trickle down method. When person X get equipment a which replaces equipment peice b they have to offer b to the raid. If b is worth too much for them to offer than maybe they should not roll and get a . . .<br>
<br>
This is how many big guilds do it. This way, 1 win becomes a win for many folks.<br>
<br>
Without this, lets say a kael bp drops, warrior with cobalt bp upgrades then sells cobalt. So they get 2 wins. Now if the trickle down works then the cobalt goes up for roll, someone with hate bp gets it, hate bp goes up for roll, someone with crafted gets , person with crafted bp well if no one wants maybe it goes to raid organisers to be sold to cover dots and ports etc.<br>
<br>
Honestly I am amazed and impressed that less of this sort of thing has happened on the open raids here, says a lot about the folks here that this does not happen all the while.<br>
<br>
Often, stuff that happens on open raids is what leeds to one of the justifications for guilds :-)<br>
<br>
Personaly, loot wise, by randomly giving items to everyone who can use you slow down the speed at which the raid group can move forward.<br>
<br>
Equiping the main tank with the best armor and weapons makes a lot of sense. Never been anywhere near the top of the food chain in terms of equipment on any server but the idea is sound.<br>
<br>
Lets say it takes 1 month per place to get 1 suit of armor and assume we have 6 tanks.<br>
<br>
With the give to main tank method  you will be fighting at the 6th lvl place after 6 months. (6th lvl means 1 &gt; 2 &gt; 3 etc. 6th place is alot harder than the 1st place. 1st place normaly hate.<br>
